---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="AIGIS | Levenhall" description="AIGIS is Levenhall's modular, containerized AI evaluation and governance platform — designed to run from unclassified through TS/SCI air-gapped on identical container images.">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="a-hero">
        <div class="a-hero-bg"></div>
        <div class="a-hero-grid"></div>
        <div class="a-hero-inner">
            <p class="a-tag">A Levenhall Product</p>
            <h1 class="a-wordmark">AIGIS</h1>
            <p class="a-tagline">AI evaluation &amp; governance, from unclassified to TS/SCI &mdash; on the same container.</p>
            <div class="a-cta">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-gold">Request Early Access</a>
                <a href="#deploy" class="btn btn-outline-white">See the Deployment Story</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE SHIELD ── -->
    <section class="a-section a-shield">
        <div class="a-narrow reveal">
            <p class="a-lede"><span class="a-drop">A</span>IGIS takes its name from the mythological <em>aegis</em> &mdash; the shield Athena carried. The function follows the name.</p>
            <p>For every AI system you intend to deploy, there is exactly one question that matters: <em>is this model safe and mission-ready for this user, on this network, doing this mission, at this classification level?</em></p>
            <p>AIGIS is the operational evaluator's answer to that question. Not a research bench. Not a one-off pilot. A continuous infrastructure that asks the question every time, and tells you when the answer changes.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE GAP ── -->
    <section class="a-section a-gap">
        <div class="a-gap-bg"></div>
        <div class="a-gap-inner">
            <div class="a-gap-header reveal">
                <span class="a-eyebrow a-eyebrow-dark">§ Why we built it</span>
                <h2>The gap between the research bench and the program shelf.</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="a-gap-prose reveal">
                <p>If you evaluate AI in a defense or intelligence context today, you choose between two unsatisfying options.</p>
                <p>The first is <strong>research-grade</strong> &mdash; HELM, Inspect, lm-evaluation-harness. These are excellent tools, designed by and for ML researchers. They were never designed to deploy on classified networks, never expected to express operational context, and don't pretend otherwise.</p>
                <p>The second is <strong>program-proprietary</strong> &mdash; a benchmark suite built inside a single program for that program's mission, alive for as long as that program is alive. When the program ends, the institutional knowledge ends with it.</p>
                <p>AIGIS is the third option. <strong>Vendor-agnostic, cross-classification, continuous</strong> &mdash; designed from the start to deploy across DoD, IC, and commercial environments without changing platforms, and to outlive any one program.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THE DEPLOYMENT STORY (THE STAR) ── -->
    <section class="a-section a-deploy" id="deploy">
        <div class="a-narrow reveal">
            <span class="a-eyebrow">§ The killer feature</span>
            <h2>Same container. Every network.</h2>
            <p class="a-deploy-lede">The image that runs in an unclassified Kubernetes cluster is the same image that runs air-gapped on JWICS. The only thing that changes is Helm.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="a-deploy-tabs reveal">
            <div class="a-tab a-tab-active">
                <span class="a-tab-label">unclass.yaml</span>
                <pre class="a-code"><span class="a-c-key">llm</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">provider</span>: <span class="a-c-val">openai</span>
  <span class="a-c-key">model</span>: <span class="a-c-val">gpt-4o</span>
<span class="a-c-key">vector</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">backend</span>: <span class="a-c-val">managed-cloud</span>
<span class="a-c-key">network</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">egress</span>: <span class="a-c-val">full</span></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="a-tab">
                <span class="a-tab-label">il5.yaml</span>
                <pre class="a-code"><span class="a-c-key">llm</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">provider</span>: <span class="a-c-val">openai-fedramp</span>
  <span class="a-c-key">model</span>: <span class="a-c-val">gpt-4o</span>
<span class="a-c-key">vector</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">backend</span>: <span class="a-c-val">pgvector</span>
<span class="a-c-key">network</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">egress</span>: <span class="a-c-val">restricted</span></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="a-tab">
                <span class="a-tab-label">tssci.yaml</span>
                <pre class="a-code"><span class="a-c-key">llm</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">provider</span>: <span class="a-c-val">ollama</span>
  <span class="a-c-key">model</span>: <span class="a-c-val">llama3-70b-q4</span>
<span class="a-c-key">vector</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">backend</span>: <span class="a-c-val">pgvector</span>
<span class="a-c-key">network</span>:
  <span class="a-c-key">egress</span>: <span class="a-c-val">none</span></pre>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="a-deploy-footer reveal">
            <p>Three deployments. One image. The model weights, benchmark suites, and knowledge base ship as container volumes for the air-gapped cases. K3s for the tactical edge. Everything underneath is open-source &mdash; no vendor lock-in at the layer that matters.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── WHAT IT DOES — THREE TRACKS ── -->
    <section class="a-section a-tracks">
        <div class="a-narrow reveal">
            <span class="a-eyebrow">§ What it does</span>
            <h2>Three tracks running off one harness.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="a-tracks-grid reveal">
            <article class="a-track">
                <span class="a-track-num">I.</span>
                <h3>Evaluation</h3>
                <p>Adapters for OpenAI, HuggingFace, Bedrock, gRPC, and local Ollama behind one uniform protocol. Pluggable scorers covering exact match, similarity, classification, and routed human evaluation. Every run captures a full environment snapshot for reproducibility &mdash; Python version, AIGIS version, provider, timestamp.</p>
                <p>Domain coverage: general, safety, adversarial, agentic, multimodal, DDIL, and mission-specific.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="a-track">
                <span class="a-track-num">II.</span>
                <h3>Adversarial &amp; Operational Stress</h3>
                <p>An automated red-teaming pipeline aligned to MITRE ATLAS &mdash; prompt injection, jailbreak generation, data-poisoning probes, model-extraction resistance &mdash; with results mapped to ATLAS technique IDs.</p>
                <p>A DDIL conditions simulator that injects latency, jitter, throttling, and intermittent connectivity, then measures degradation curves instead of binary pass/fail. Agentic evaluation captures the full execution trace and scores against OWASP Agentic AI Top 10 and the MAESTRO framework.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="a-track">
                <span class="a-track-num">III.</span>
                <h3>Governance &amp; Risk</h3>
                <p>Live compliance coverage against NIST AI RMF, MITRE ATLAS, EU AI Act, ISO 42001, OWASP Agentic AI Top 10, and the DoD AI Ethical Principles. Risk scoring against active incidents. Insurance coverage monitoring. An activity feed that surfaces evaluation results, adversarial detections, and bias audits in real time.</p>
                <p>Human evaluation rounds out the stack &mdash; Likert, pairwise, best-of-N, with Krippendorff's alpha and Fleiss' kappa computed for inter-rater reliability.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── CTA ── -->
    <section class="a-cta-section">
        <div class="a-cta-bg"></div>
        <div class="a-cta-inner">
            <div class="a-cta-rule"></div>
            <p class="a-cta-eyebrow">Levenhall Proprietary</p>
            <h2>AIGIS is active. Early access is selective.</h2>
            <p>We work with DoD and IC organizations, regulated commercial customers, and insurance counterparties. The platform architecture, adapter SDK, governance-integrated scoring, DDIL profiling, and benchmark methodology are Levenhall proprietary.</p>
            <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-gold">Request Early Access</a>
                <a href="/services#market-intelligence" class="btn btn-outline-white">Intelligence Practice</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ── HERO ── */
    .a-hero {
        background: linear-gradient(160deg, #04070e 0%, #080e1c 30%, #0f1f3a 70%, #0c1628 100%);
        padding: 9rem 2rem 5rem;
        text-align: center;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .a-hero-bg {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image:
            radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 50%, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.05) 0%, transparent 50%),
            radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.06) 0%, transparent 50%);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .a-hero-grid {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image:
            linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 1px, transparent 1px),
            linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.012) 1px, transparent 1px);
        background-size: 60px 60px;
        pointer-events: none;
        mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 25%, transparent 75%);
        -webkit-mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, black 25%, transparent 75%);
    }

    .a-hero::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.5), transparent);
        opacity: 0.55;
    }

    .a-hero-inner {
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .a-tag {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        letter-spacing: 3.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .a-wordmark {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-size: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 6.5rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 16px;
        color: #fff;
        line-height: 1;
        margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
        text-indent: 16px;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fff 40%, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.5) 100%);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        background-clip: text;
    }

    .a-tagline {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .a-cta {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    /* ── SHARED ── */
    .a-section {
        padding: 6rem 0;
    }

    .a-narrow {
        max-width: 660px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .a-eyebrow {
        display: block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 2.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
    }

    .a-eyebrow-dark { color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.85); }

    .a-narrow h2 {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.3rem);
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
    }

    /* ── SHIELD ── */
    .a-shield {
        background: var(--cream);
    }

    .a-lede {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: 1.55rem;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .a-drop {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 0.85;
        float: left;
        padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem 0 0;
    }

    .a-shield p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    .a-shield em {
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--burgundy);
    }

    /* ── GAP ── */
    .a-gap {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a1628 0%, var(--deep-navy) 100%);
        padding: 6rem 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .a-gap-bg {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 70%, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.04) 0%, transparent 50%);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .a-gap::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.3);
    }

    .a-gap-inner {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .a-gap-header {
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        padding-bottom: 1.8rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .a-gap-header h2 {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.3rem);
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: #fff;
        margin: 0;
        font-weight: 700;
    }

    .a-gap-prose p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
        margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    }

    .a-gap-prose strong {
        color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.95);
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* ── DEPLOYMENT (THE KILLER FEATURE) ── */
    .a-deploy {
        background: var(--stone);
        padding: 6rem 0 6.5rem;
    }

    .a-deploy-lede {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--burgundy);
        line-height: 1.55;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .a-deploy-tabs {
        max-width: 960px;
        margin: 3rem auto 2.5rem;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 1rem;
    }

    .a-tab {
        background: #0a1628;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
        overflow: hidden;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .a-tab-active {
        border-color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.4);
        box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.15);
    }

    .a-tab:hover {
        border-color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.3);
    }

    .a-tab-label {
        display: block;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
        padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Menlo', 'Consolas', monospace;
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.85);
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .a-code {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 1.2rem 1.2rem;
        font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Menlo', 'Consolas', monospace;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
        white-space: pre;
        overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .a-c-key {
        color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.85);
    }

    .a-c-val {
        color: var(--gold);
    }

    .a-deploy-footer {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .a-deploy-footer p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--text-medium);
    }

    /* ── TRACKS ── */
    .a-tracks {
        background: var(--cream);
    }

    .a-tracks-grid {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .a-track {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
        gap: 2rem;
        padding: 2.4rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(30, 58, 95, 0.12);
    }

    .a-track:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    .a-track-num {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 1;
        text-align: right;
        padding-top: 0.4rem;
    }

    .a-track h3 {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.3;
    }

    .a-track p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .a-track p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    /* ── CTA ── */
    .a-cta-section {
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #060b16 0%, var(--deep-navy) 50%, #162d4f 100%);
        padding: 5.5rem 2rem;
        text-align: center;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .a-cta-bg {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image:
            radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 50%, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.06) 0%, transparent 50%),
            radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.04) 0%, transparent 40%);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .a-cta-section::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.5), transparent);
    }

    .a-cta-inner {
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .a-cta-rule {
        width: 30px;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--gold);
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    }

    .a-cta-eyebrow {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 3px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: rgba(56, 217, 201, 0.85);
        margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
    }

    .a-cta-section h2 {
        font-family: 'Crimson Text', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.25;
    }

    .a-cta-section p {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
        font-size: 1.02rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .a-hero { padding: 7rem 2rem 4rem; }
        .a-section { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .a-deploy { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .a-gap { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .a-deploy-tabs { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.8rem; }
        .a-code { font-size: 0.78rem; }
        .a-lede { font-size: 1.25rem; }
        .a-drop { font-size: 2.4rem; }
        .a-track { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.6rem; padding: 2rem 0; }
        .a-track-num { text-align: left; font-size: 2rem; padding-top: 0; }
    }
</style>
